On 28 January 1961, Rwanda [[Abolition of monarchy|abolished its monarchy]] and became a republic, during the [[Rwandan Revolution]]. Afterwards, Kigeli V Ndahindurwa continued to maintain his claim to the throne until his death on 16 October 2016 in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=washingtonpost>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/africa/kigeli-v-ndahindurwa-rwandan-king-without-a-crown-dies-at-80/2016/10/18/c02e6a22-948a-11e6-bb29-bf2701dbe0a3_story.html |title= Kigeli V Ndahindurwa, Rwandan king without a crown, dies at 80 |work=The Washington Post |date=18 October 2016}}</ref> On 9 January 2017, the Royal Council of [[Abiru]] announced Prince [[Emmanuel Bushayija]] as the new heir to the throne. Prince Emmanuel adopted the [[regnal name]] Yuhi VI.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/12/rwandas-new-king-former-pepsi-salesman-residing-cheshire/|title=Rwanda's new king is former Pepsi salesman residing in Cheshire|author=Adrian Blomfield|date=12 January 2017|work=the Daily Telegraph|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>

